NAME
    ldg_getpath - returns the real own path of a shared lib.

SYNOPSIS
   char* ldg_init( void);

PARAMETERS
      return : buffer containing the current library path.

DESCRIPTION
    This function returns the real path of a library. It can
    be called only inside a LDG-library and outside the
    main function. The reason is the path is not initialised
    during the first execution of a library (i.e. when the
    main() function is executed). So ldg_getpath() can only be
    invoked inside a library function.

SEE ALSO
    ldg_libpath()

